{"title": "Usage of hard-coded secret", "summary": "  Code is not a safe place to store secrets. Use environment variables or a secret management system instead. ", "description": "\n\nCode is not a safe place to store secrets. Use environment variables or a secret management system instead.\n", "recommendations": "\n\n\u274c Do not store plaintext secrets in your code\n\n```javascript\n app.use(\n  session({\n    secret: \"shh-my-secret\",\n    name: \"my-custom-session-name\",\n  })\n)\n```\n\n\u2705 Use environment variables\n\n```javascript\n app.use(\n  session({\n    secret: process.env.secret,\n    name: \"my-custom-session-name\",\n  })\n)\n```\n\n\u2705 Use a secret management system or even better, a key management service (KMS) with encryption\n", "taxonomy": ["CWE-798"], "references": ["https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/javascript_express_hardcoded_secret", "https://owasp.org/www-community/vulnerabilities/Use_of_hard-coded_password", "https://cloud.google.com/kms/docs", "https://aws.amazon.com/kms/"], "details": "{% include '../generic_bandit_issue/details' %}"}